                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00">Good eye. It does say &quot;GOVT EXPER <i>with</i> OSS&quot; (emphasis on &#x27;with&#x27;) rather than &quot;XYZ <i>of</i> OSS&quot;, implying some sort of external role – such as helping establish chain of command in the early days, or some other bureaucratic help. A glance at the register itself shows that most OSS involvement is cited with the &quot;of&quot; convention: <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;archive.org&#x2F;stream&#x2F;biographicregist1950unit&#x2F;biographicregist1950unit_djvu.txt" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;archive.org&#x2F;stream&#x2F;biographicregist1950unit&#x2F;biograph...</a> (BR, 1950 edition)<span>
