                  <span class="c00">Having worked with some departments where the average age was 50+ I&#x27;ve definitely seen flagrant rule bending for risky behavior (e.g. not carrying radiation detectors, working on roofs without proper &quot;safety&quot; equipment, etc). The thing is these people got the job done. The younger generation (which I belong to) would likely throw up their hands and claim they couldn&#x27;t complete the task because some prerequisite for a rule wasn&#x27;t in place.<span>
